Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Pat @Maple Leaf Farms Duck Breasts{2} dry with #paper towels{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place skin sides down in a large, preferably nonstick, pan. Cook over medium heat until skin is crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}, carefully pouring out fat as it's released (don't flip duck just yet).

Meanwhile, trim and halve @Baby Carrots{8} lengthwise. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender and slightly browned at edges, ~{20-25%minutes}. While carrots roast, trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{1%minute}. Stir in @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup} and @water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Cherry Jam{2%tbsp}, @Chicken Demi-Glace{1}, @Ancho Chili Powder{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Once skin is crisp, flip over duck in pan. Pour in jam mixture and add @Dried Cherries{1}. Let simmer until sauce is thick and duck is cooked to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes}. Leaving sauce in pan, transfer duck to a #cutting board{}.

> If sauce is too thick, add a tablespoon or two of water (double for 4 servings).

Reduce heat under pan with sauce to low and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Once butter has melted, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; turn off heat and set aside. Fluff rice with a #fork{}, then stir in @Pistachios{1}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice duck crosswise; divide between plates with rice. Pour sauce over duck. Serve with carrots on the side. Garnish with scallion greens.